cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.AI

This paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method uses adversarial training and a cycle-consistency constraint, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions speech recognition as an application, which falls under the sub-category of speech processing (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to enforcing cycle-consistency, which can be seen as a contribution to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
